        <prompt>What was the primary impact of the Teapot Dome scandal?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It improved oil production</option>
            <option letter="b">It exposed government corruption</option>
            <option letter="c">It created new regulations</option>
            <option letter="d">It increased presidential power</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Teapot Dome scandal exposed corruption in Harding's administration, revealing the illegal leasing of naval oil reserves and leading to the first conviction of a cabinet member for a crime committed in office.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>How did Native American boarding schools affect tribal communities?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">They preserved tribal cultures</option>
            <option letter="b">They forced cultural assimilation</option>
            <option letter="c">They improved tribal economies</option>
            <option letter="d">They increased tribal autonomy</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Native American boarding schools forcibly assimilated Native children by removing them from their families, forbidding their languages and customs, and attempting to erase their cultural identities.</explanation>
    </question>

