        <prompt>What was the main goal of the Antiquities Act of 1906?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To sell federal lands</option>
            <option letter="b">To protect historical sites</option>
            <option letter="c">To build museums</option>
            <option letter="d">To fund archaeology</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Antiquities Act of 1906 gave presidents the power to protect historical and natural sites as national monuments, significantly expanding federal conservation efforts.</explanation>
