    <question>
        <prompt>What characterized the relationship between Theodore Roosevelt and the press?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">He avoided all contact</option>
            <option letter="b">He actively managed media relations</option>
            <option letter="c">He censored newspapers</option>
            <option letter="d">He ignored the press</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Roosevelt actively managed his relationship with the press, giving reporters unprecedented access, using them to promote his policies, and becoming the first president to make media relations a priority.</explanation>
