    <question>
        <prompt>How did the Federal Farm Loan Act affect American farmers?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It eliminated all farm loans</option>
            <option letter="b">It provided easier access to credit</option>
            <option letter="c">It raised interest rates</option>
            <option letter="d">It reduced farm production</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Federal Farm Loan Act of 1916 created a network of land banks that provided farmers with easier access to credit at lower interest rates, helping to stabilize agricultural financing.</explanation>
